<P>See how to link all your digital devices together.</P>
<P>A special 1394 Pavilion hosted by 1394 Trade Association will be highlighted at CES. More than two dozen companies will demonstrate compelling 1394 connectivity among all types of audio, video and control products.</P>
<P>What does 1394 mean to the consumer technology industry?  It means fully functional digital programming, delivery and devices.</P>
<P>The consumer electronics industry and the cable television industry reached an agreement in November 1998 and completed the necessary extensions to the baseline IEEE-1394 specification (the so-called "firewire") to promote compatibility between digital television receivers and digital set-top boxes. </P>
<P>Having now completed the baseline specification 
      for this digital interface, the consumer electronics and cable industries believe that some consumer electronics manufacturers may produce 1394-enabled digital television receivers with content protection technology for retail distribution by November 1999.</P>
<P>In addition, the two industries have committed to continue working together to complete the work that will ensure that copyrighted material sent over this digital link is protected, in recognition of the concerns of the Motion Picture Association of America  (MPAA). </P>
